        <div class="text-contents d-flex gap-3 flex-column"><h2 class="h2-big">How Does a Virtual Orthopedic Consultation Work?</h2><p>A virtual orthopedic consultation simplifies the process of receiving expert medical advice without the need for physical travel, making it highly accessible for patients regardless of their location. After scheduling a telehealth consultation, patients are scheduled for a video conference with an orthopedic specialist. This digital appointment allows for a comprehensive discussion about the patient's condition, symptoms, and medical history, including any prior treatments or surgeries. </p><p>Prior to the consultation, patients are often encouraged to upload or share relevant medical documents, such as X-rays, MRI scans, or previous medical reports, to provide a thorough background for the specialist. During the appointment, the specialist might request the patient to perform certain movements or exercises to assess the range of motion, strength, and areas of discomfort directly. This interactive evaluation helps in forming an accurate diagnosis and crafting a personalized treatment plan. </p><p>Depending on the findings, Dr. Lawyer may suggest a specific treatment option depending on the orthopedic issue. This may include physical therapy, or further diagnostic tests to identify the issue. The goal is to offer a seamless and effective road to recovery, ensuring patients receive high-quality orthopedic care tailored to their individual needs, all from the comfort of their home.</p><a href="#" class="btn btn-card mt-0">How To Schedule With A Virtual Orthopedic</a></div>
